 recent developments in the area of cognitive and functional linguistics: 1) form in language always has a relation to meaning, 2) a categorical approach to language is replaced with an understanding of language as a gradient phenomenon, which is investigated via statistics, 3) grammar is seen as a usage-based phenomenon. Throughout the book we see that each of the profiles determines a correlation between certain forms and certain meanings. By studying the distribution of different forms we can uncover the semantic restrictions standing behind them.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aCognitive grammar. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxApplied LinguisticsxQuantitative, Computational, and Corpus Linguistics. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxLevels of Linguistic AnalysisxSemantics. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxLevels of Linguistic AnalysisxSyntax. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxTheoretical Frameworks and DisciplinesxCognitive Linguistics. 0aLinguisticsxStatistical methods. 0aRussian languagexWord frequency. 4aConstruction. 4aCorpus. 4aQuantitative. 4aRussian. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103934840 cprintz978311035553640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036185840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110361858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110361858.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_